// bridge_stream_char_axil_mon_cfg — auto-generated bridge monitor cfg space.
//
// Generated by bridge_pkg/generators/cfg_rdl_generator.py from the
// adapter list of bridge_stream_char_axil_mon. Backed by an AXI4-Lite slave
// (cpuif=axi4-lite-flat); the bridge top instantiates the emitted
// regblock and routes hwif_out fields to its internal cfg_* nets.
//
// Field schema mirrors the bridge generator's MONITOR_CFG_SIGNALS
// list (single source of truth in axi4_timing_wrapper_component.py).
// Per-direction register layout:
//
//   +0x00  CTRL     enables[6:0] + timeout_cycles[31:16]
//   +0x04  LATENCY  latency_threshold[31:0]
//   +0x08  MASKS_A  axi_pkt_mask     + axi_err_select
//   +0x0C  MASKS_B  axi_error_mask   + axi_timeout_mask
//   +0x10  MASKS_C  axi_compl_mask   + axi_thresh_mask
//   +0x14  MASKS_D  axi_perf_mask    + axi_addr_mask
//   +0x18  MASKS_E  axi_debug_mask   (upper 16b reserved)
//
// Conditional clusters:
//   - WINDOW   emitted when the monitor's perf logic is enabled
//   - ADDR_RNG emitted when N_ADDR_RANGES > 0 for that monitor

addrmap bridge_stream_char_axil_mon_cfg {
    name = "bridge_stream_char_axil_mon monitor cfg";
    desc = "AXIL-mapped cfg backing the bridge's monitor enables, masks, window control, and address-range checker.";

